      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "THE FINAL DANCE (7) is first up for seven weeks and has joined the powerhouse Emma Stewart yard in that time. Looks wlel placed to kick off for the new stable with a win. GLENLINE (3) added to a string of good performances last time out when he came from the back row and finished runner-up at this venue. Rises in grade but he came from wider than this when edged out at Bendigo prior and should have no excuses from this advantageous draw. GOZO MAJOR (1) has been racing well of late, producing a couple of nice efforts since a win at Ararat. Drew wider and did some work when fourth at his latest appearance at Bendigo, beaten 4.4 metres. Should enjoy the favours from the inside barrier. IM THE REASON (12) showed some decent form last time including a Melton win two back. Tough draw for the return but looks ready to go off two nice trials.",
